<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Eric</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-01-19 18:18:41</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>The Goblin Preacher is a rare spawn in Perma Frost. 3 out of 4 times a placeholder will spawn in his spot. His spawn site is 25 to 30 minutes. The Circlet is a rare drop, dropping once in 12 or so drops. He has a uncommon drop of the Cold Iron Mace once in every 4 to 6 drops.<BR>
<BR>
The Preacher is 24th to 26th level, Cleric based. If you're on a crowded server, chances are the room is camped 24/7. On the less crowded servers like PVP or Team, getting the circlet is far easier.<BR>
<BR>
The circlet has a chainmail look on all classes.</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Not Impressed</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-02-14 09:22:43</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Bah, me and some friends strolled into Perma and walked away with a Circlet each plus 2 Cold Iron Morningstars.  And that was on one of the five oldest and most populated servers.  Just go in with a group you can trust to know their stuff, where everyone knows their place in the group.  No prob.  Oh and yeah, to the post above.  Runed Circlet plus plat would be expected in trade for some SplitPaw Gloves.  Hand armor that gives a wis bonus is a big deal =).  </font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Lenaddar Anatar of Povar</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-04-06 11:23:15</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Let me set the record straight. The circlet is a common drop,<BR>
Morningstar is rare. <BR>
<BR>
How to get the Preacher to spawn, about once an hour maybe<BR>
less as I wasnt timing him. This room was all green to me at<BR>
46 and I soloed the entire room for 7 hours before I had<BR>
enough and didnt wish to appear to be farming - which I was<BR>
but for my guild. No one was in the zone at the time I<BR>
started so don't flame me for the farming aspect.<BR>
<BR>
Once the spawn is broken there will be 8 spawn sights. Chances<BR>
are you won't find the Preacher when you come in. Heres how.<BR>
One to three Ice Gobblins, maybe a priest in the back toward<BR>
the door to the sub level - nothing really down thier but <BR>
good exp till your mid 40s or less. Take them out first. This<BR>
seems to be key. Next One or two "gobbos" will spawn in the <BR>
Preacher room at different times - take them out and wait.<BR>
<BR>
Next spawn will be two gobbos up front at the entrance to the<BR>
room. Take them out. Wait. Lots of waiting here. By the time <BR>
I was nearing full mana the single preacher would spawn in the<BR>
room and Blast, stun, maybe another blast at 614 and 50, <BR>
respectively and hes done. Go loot your goodie. He also may<BR>
drop a piece of bronze armor. FS is very rare, bronze <BR>
uncommon and Rusty common. I did this for 7 hours, heres what<BR>
I got: 5 Circlets and 1 Cold Iron Morningstar. Not bad for <BR>
the amount of work I put into it. Twice left to go get a Heart<BR>
of Frost and an Icy Greaves. Guess what? The preacher did not<BR>
spawn as expected and I had to start the cycle over from<BR>
scratch. So doing this in cycle is the key.<BR>
<BR>
Lenaddar Anatar of Povar<BR>
46th level Wizard</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Alielgo</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-04-19 23:57:28</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>I can confirm, at least on Povar, the CIMS is becoming the rare drop, the Circlet the common drop.  I have camped the Preacher numerous times over the past month, and in that time I have seen about 15-20 Circlets.  I've seen exactly two CIMS.  Circlet is worth 3x more than the CIMS as well.<BR>
<BR>
Whether or not this is just bug in the Preacher code, I have no clue...<BR>
<BR>
As for getting the Preacher to spawn, it is like everything else in Perma, completely random.  Spawn time on all spawns (excepting Vox of course) is approx. 24 minutes.<BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: dordamer</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-04-26 16:23:38</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>i got the circlet last night.  the trick to making the preacher spawn is not being in the room he spawns in.  try sitting in the little hall on the bottom lvl.  we got 2 circlets, each time the preacher spawned.  he and his placeholders are on a 24 min spawn.  oh yeah and perma wasnt that crowded, there was my group and like 3 others in the zone.  we camped it with a lvl 31, me, as the high and 2 shamans in the group too<BR>
<BR>
good luck ;-)</font></td></tr></table>
